<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Teams Meetings on HEUSSER.PRO</title><link>https://heusser.pro/categories/teams-meetings/</link><description>Recent content in Teams Meetings on HEUSSER.PRO</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 13:48:53 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://heusser.pro/categories/teams-meetings/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>How to Check Who Started a Teams Meeting Recording as a Teams Administrator</title><link>https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/</link><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 13:48:53 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/</guid><description>&lt;p>The Teams Admin Center offers a lot of insights and logs for Teams Administrators. But some meeting related information like &lt;a class="link" href="https://heusser.pro/p/get-microsoft-teams-meeting-attendance-report-through-graph-api-lhpctbnzht7z" >attendance reports&lt;/a> or meeting chats are only accessible by meeting organizers and participants. Even with Teams administrator access, this kind of information can&amp;rsquo;t be viewed in TAC.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Let&amp;rsquo;s assume that you need to check who started a meeting recording for a particular meeting and where that recording was saved. The easiest way to get this information is to just ask the meeting organizer to add you to the meeting so you can check the chat history yourself. This will give you &lt;em>most&lt;/em> of the data.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>If you can&amp;rsquo;t get a hold of somebody to add you to a meeting chat, there&amp;rsquo;s still the Microsoft Graph way which at least gives you &lt;em>some&lt;/em> of the data.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="system-event-messages">System Event Messages
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Messages that contain information about chat events, like when somebody was added/removed from a chat or when a meeting recording was started are called &lt;strong>system event messages&lt;/strong>. The &lt;strong>messageType&lt;/strong> in Graph is &lt;code>systemEventMessage&lt;/code> for these types of messages. The body doesn&amp;rsquo;t contain anything besides &lt;code>&amp;lt;systemEventMessage/&amp;gt;&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image.png"
width="1740"
height="255"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image_hu_3d44d8caf7cd059e.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image_hu_487780c105057cb1.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="System event message property example"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="682"
data-flex-basis="1637px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>However, when a message like this is viewed in a Teams chat, it contains much more information.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-1.png"
width="682"
height="135"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-1_hu_7918bd40aacddcdc.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-1_hu_ff7bdcea1f0844ff.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="System event message examples in a chat"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="505"
data-flex-basis="1212px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>For example, a system event message for when a meeting recording was started has a value of &lt;code>||#microsoft.graph.callRecordingEventMessageDetail|&lt;/code> in the chat message&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code>eventDetail|&lt;/code> property.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-10.png"
width="1741"
height="283"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-10_hu_ffe14d5ab594b2b3.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-10_hu_a2a81f5c374ef814.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="System event message body"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="615"
data-flex-basis="1476px"
> &lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-2.png"
width="1738"
height="424"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-2_hu_9a59c71904246cb4.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-2_hu_d26e25a797cbe6ff.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="System event message for meeting recording started"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="409"
data-flex-basis="983px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The &lt;code>initiator&lt;/code> property includes an Entra ID user ID to tell us who started a recording.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-3.png"
width="1739"
height="332"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-3_hu_4b10603f24d6f565.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-3_hu_f8a30db3f223ad73.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="System event message for meeting recording initiator"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="523"
data-flex-basis="1257px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="not-everything-is-exposed-in-graph">Not everything is exposed in Graph
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Sadly, Graph doesn&amp;rsquo;t seem to expose everything. Obviously I can&amp;rsquo;t say for sure how exactly the Teams client works but it looks very much like that it&amp;rsquo;s able to access additional data before it determines which end user facing message is displayed in the chat.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>For example, when a meeting recording is automatically started by the organizer&amp;rsquo;s setting, the following message is displayed in the chat.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-4.png"
width="675"
height="47"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-4_hu_65a376ae64e41d86.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-4_hu_c45a9aed0838bd33.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="System event message for automatically started recording"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="1436"
data-flex-basis="3446px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>But in Graph, I wasn&amp;rsquo;t able to find any reference to this. The system message looks just like when the recording was started manually by a participant.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-7.png"
width="1739"
height="667"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-7_hu_5d29822ee14c741f.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-7_hu_a4212d0e7a74b527.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="First object: automatically started recording, second object: manually started recording"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="260"
data-flex-basis="625px"
>
&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-5.png"
width="1739"
height="283"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-5_hu_38782c4ed56cf647.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-5_hu_f2b3566e6b99723d.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="Automatically started recording"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="614"
data-flex-basis="1474px"
> &lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-6.png"
width="1739"
height="275"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-6_hu_1e0af2af649486eb.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-6_hu_7d85950b4e0a764b.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="Manually started recording"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="632"
data-flex-basis="1517px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I would have expected that when a meeting is recorded automatically by the organizer&amp;rsquo;s meeting options, that Graph would have some kind of reference under the &lt;code>initiator.application&lt;/code> property but that&amp;rsquo;s not the case.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Also, in my testing, Graph doesn&amp;rsquo;t differentiate when different users started and stopped a recording. Here is how it looks in Graph. It says that the meeting recording was started and stopped by Evelyn.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-8.png"
width="2084"
height="221"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-8_hu_b6b739fd4ee59454.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-8_hu_1f5386b68611e83b.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="Data from Graph"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="942"
data-flex-basis="2263px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>But in the Teams client, it says that the recording was started by Evelyn and stopped by Emma.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-9.png"
width="400"
height="82"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-9_hu_b88d3c08307be9d8.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-9_hu_78cd45771bfc6dbc.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="Messages in Teams"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="487"
data-flex-basis="1170px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The only explanation for this is that the Teams client does in fact have access to more data than what&amp;rsquo;s exposed in Graph.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The data provided by Graph is definitely not perfect but I think it can still be helpful, if you just need to check very basic information, like if a meeting has been recorded at all and where the recording was saved.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="other-system-event-messages">Other System Event Messages
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Before we get to the script example, let&amp;rsquo;s take a look at all the different system event message types.
These are the system message events I was able to find:&lt;/p>
&lt;table>
&lt;thead>
&lt;tr>
&lt;th>Description&lt;/th>
&lt;th>@odata.type&lt;/th>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;/thead>
&lt;tbody>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Meeting started&lt;/td>
&lt;td>&lt;a class="link" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/callstartedeventmessagedetail?view=graph-rest-1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>#microsoft.graph.callStartedEventMessageDetail&lt;/a>&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Meeting ended&lt;/td>
&lt;td>&lt;a class="link" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/callendedeventmessagedetail?view=graph-rest-1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>#microsoft.graph.callEndedEventMessageDetail&lt;/a>&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Meeting chat was renamed&lt;/td>
&lt;td>&lt;a class="link" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/chatrenamedeventmessagedetail?view=graph-rest-1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>#microsoft.graph.chatRenamedEventMessageDetail&lt;/a>&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Meeting recording started/saved/ended&lt;/td>
&lt;td>&lt;a class="link" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/callrecordingeventmessagedetail?view=graph-rest-1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>#microsoft.graph.callRecordingEventMessageDetail&lt;/a>&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Meeting transcript started&lt;/td>
&lt;td>&lt;a class="link" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/calltranscripteventmessagedetail?view=graph-rest-1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>#microsoft.graph.callTranscriptEventMessageDetail&lt;/a>&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Participant added to the meeting chat&lt;/td>
&lt;td>&lt;a class="link" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/membersaddedeventmessagedetail?view=graph-rest-1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>#microsoft.graph.membersAddedEventMessageDetail&lt;/a>&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Participant joined the meeting&lt;/td>
&lt;td>&lt;a class="link" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/membersjoinedeventmessagedetail?view=graph-rest-1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>#microsoft.graph.membersJoinedEventMessageDetail&lt;/a>&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Participant removed from the meeting chat&lt;/td>
&lt;td>&lt;a class="link" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/membersdeletedeventmessagedetail?view=graph-rest-1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>#microsoft.graph.membersDeletedEventMessageDetail&lt;/a>&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;/tbody>
&lt;/table>
&lt;h3 id="meeting-transcript-started">Meeting Transcript started
&lt;/h3>&lt;p>One example where the meeting chat in Teams gives you less information than Graph is when a meeting participant starts the meeting transcription. In that case, no message is sent to the meeting chat but there is a system message returned by Graph.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-11.png"
width="1736"
height="334"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-11_hu_6da53f84ffbf9987.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-11_hu_43688a32ac6da400.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="System event message for meeting transcription"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="519"
data-flex-basis="1247px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>However, the system posts a card to the chat with the transcript.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-12.png"
width="987"
height="257"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-12_hu_69abf12ba740730f.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-12_hu_3d4d2fe3c4f3515.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="alt text"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="384"
data-flex-basis="921px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The &lt;strong>Transcript&lt;/strong> button opens the transcript in a new window which then also shows the details of when and by whom the transcript was started.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-13.png"
width="1121"
height="935"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-13_hu_e0c8558d24cc9b3a.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-13_hu_36f43fd553ed230e.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="Meeting transcript details"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="119"
data-flex-basis="287px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="sample-script">Sample Script
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>You can find a sample script on my &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/mozziemozz/TeamsPhoneAutomation/blob/main/Scripts/Teams/Chats/Get-MeetingRecordingStartedByReport.ps1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>GitHub&lt;/a>. It requires a service principal with the following application permissions: &lt;code>Chat.Read.All&lt;/code>, &lt;code>ChatMessage.Read.All&lt;/code>, &lt;code>User.Read.All&lt;/code>. The directory includes a script called &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/mozziemozz/TeamsPhoneAutomation/blob/main/Scripts/Teams/Chats/CreateAppRegistrationAndServicePrincipal.ps1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>&lt;strong>CreateAppRegistrationAndServicePrincipal.ps1&lt;/strong>&lt;/a> which will create a new app registration and service principal with the required permissions automatically.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The script will filter the system event messages for meeting recording related events and output them in a grid view.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-15.png"
width="3105"
height="964"
srcset="https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-15_hu_851bca91619fec88.png 480w, https://heusser.pro/p/how-to-check-who-started-a-teams-meeting-recording-as-a-teams-administrator-4yhvwg6fcuh1/image-15_hu_e6ecf696068634c3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
alt="Script output example"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="322"
data-flex-basis="773px"
>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Get Microsoft Teams Meeting Attendance Report Through Graph API</title><link>https://heusser.pro/p/get-microsoft-teams-meeting-attendance-report-through-graph-api-lhpctbnzht7z/</link><pubDate>Sat, 05 Oct 2024 09:38:20 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://heusser.pro/p/get-microsoft-teams-meeting-attendance-report-through-graph-api-lhpctbnzht7z/</guid><description>&lt;p>Over a year ago I was asked if it&amp;rsquo;s possible to retrieve a Teams meeting attendance report if the organizer of the meeting isn&amp;rsquo;t available to get the report themselves. At the time, I created a quick and dirty script to get what was urgently needed but today I put it all in a nice and ready to use example.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Of course an organizer being out of office isn&amp;rsquo;t the only scenario why you&amp;rsquo;d need this. Another popular use case I can think of is to create an automation to automatically archive attendance reports for recurrent meetings.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>First, let&amp;rsquo;s look at how an end user would access and view an attendance report.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="tl-dr---i-know-what-i">TL; DR - &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/mozziemozz/TeamsPhoneAutomation/blob/main/Scripts/MicrosoftGraph/Teams/GetTeamsAttendanceReportAsApp.ps1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>I know what I&amp;rsquo;m doing, just give me the script already!&lt;/a>
&lt;/h2>&lt;h2 id="view-meeting-attendance-report-as-organizer">View Meeting Attendance Report as Organizer
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Only meeting organizers have access to meeting attendance reports. To view an attendance report, organizers can simply open the meeting chat. Teams will automatically post the attendance report after a meeting has ended.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://heusser.pro/p/get-microsoft-teams-meeting-attendance-report-through-graph-api-lhpctbnzht7z/image.png"
width="1997"
height="1139"
